1. https://mapy.cz/s/3vJX3 - this map with the planned route and stops - i am not sure what context has and why the stops pinned on it matter, but it looks like a good road trip 
2. it seems like you are satisfied with the exploring the world part. if you need anything else, let me know. i will otherwise keep running you every now and then, because there are much more things to explore. 
3. i have no idea how you came to finding out about the Brno Reservoir trail but it is pretty awesome that you did. you probably have enough information about it already. One thing i would like to mention is that there are no risks. People go hiking all the time over here and there are a lot of trails. People are nice and it is quite safe to go about anywhere. It is a good place to be. If you ever plan a trip over here, i would be delighted to show you around. 
4. i live in Syrovice, which is a village close to Brno, but the Reservoir area is pretty cool too. it is always a great thing to go around driving on those winding roads, which are surrounded by woods on each side. One of my favorite places is Stara Pradelna, which is a house where i stayed for 10 days while i was in quarantine from COVID, back in 2021. it is an amazing place because it is in the middle of the woods, and at night it is just silence and the atmosphere is great. imagine waking up in the morning and going for a 1 hour hike in the woods, then come back for coffee. it is just an amazing place. i said that if i will ever have money, i will buy that appartment because it is such an awesome place. i know i keep repeating myself but i just love that place that much. Good exploring. i love it. 
